This paper is primarily focused on facial age estimation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves the use of deep neural networks (DNNs) and regression forests, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of image datasets (cs.MM) and likelihood functions (cs.IR) in their approach. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.IR.
